OpenUSD
-------

The package contains OpenUSD runtime files under raisim/lib/openusd and
rayrai/lib/openusd. OpenUSD is licensed by Pixar under the Tomorrow Open Source
Technology License 1.0, a modified Apache License 2.0. The upstream notice is:

Universal Scene Description
Copyright 2016 Pixar
All rights reserved.

This product includes software developed at:
Pixar (http://www.pixar.com/).

Redistributions that include OpenUSD should include the upstream OpenUSD
LICENSE.txt and NOTICE.txt files beside the OpenUSD runtime, because those
files also contain third-party dependency notices such as RapidJSON.

Bundled robot and model resources
---------------------------------

The current rsc tree includes assets with their own license files:

* rsc/go1: Unitree Robotics BSD-3-Clause notice.
* rsc/kinova: Kinova Robotics Inc. BSD-3-Clause notice.
* rsc/anymal: ANYbotics AG BSD-3-Clause notice.
* rsc/anymal_c: ANYbotics AG BSD-3-Clause notice.
* rsc/husky: Clearpath Robotics BSD-style notice.
* rsc/minitaur: Bullet/Google BSD-style notice.
* rsc/mjcf/gymnasium: Gymnasium MIT notice from OpenAI and Farama Foundation.
* rsc/aliengo and rsc/laikago: Unitree permission statements.
* rsc/cassie: the file states that no license is granted and all rights are
  reserved by the named authors.
* rsc/monkey: the file only records that the asset came from
  https://github.com/google/filament; no explicit redistribution license is
  included in this package.

The current rayrai PBR sample assets also include per-asset license files:

* AntiqueCamera, Avocado, Lantern, SciFiHelmet, and WaterBottle: glTF sample
  model license files from the KhronosGroup glTF-Sample-Assets repository.
* DamagedHelmet: model files are listed as CC-BY-4.0 and CC-BY-NC-4.0; metadata
  is listed as CC-BY-4.0.
* FlightHelmet: model files are listed as CC0-1.0 and metadata as CC-BY-4.0.
* BoomBox: README states CC0.
* MetalRoughSpheres: README and glTF metadata state CC-BY-4.0.

The asset directories should be redistributed with their local LICENSE,
README, metadata, and attribution files intact.
